    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "the `case <-c.done:` arm of this select is unhittable because a waitgroup on `run()` prevents closing the channel until this function exits.  Without that case, this Ticker/select is now the standard form covered by `c.clock.TickerFunc`. This allows you to force a tick just by advancing the clock, without the need for traps on `Reset`.\n\nHowever, you still need to set a trap on the call to `TickerFunc` itself, lest advancing the clock race with starting the ticker and leading to a flaky test.",
    "commit_id": "5df66d7e7658c14e704e12e20ba0a1cd36833343",
    "created_at": "2025-09-03T09:21:49Z",
    "diff_hunk": "@@ -198,12 +198,18 @@ func (c *Cache) run(ctx context.Context, name string, interval time.Duration, re\n \t\t\t\tlogger.Error(ctx, \"refresh metrics failed\", slog.Error(err))\n \t\t\t\tcontinue\n \t\t\t}\n-\t\t\tlogger.Debug(ctx, \"metrics refreshed\", slog.F(\"took\", time.Since(start)))\n+\t\t\tlogger.Debug(ctx, \"metrics refreshed\", slog.F(\"took\", c.clock.Since(start)))\n \t\t\tbreak\n \t\t}\n+\t}\n \n+\tdoRefresh(ctx, c.clock.Now())\n+\n+\tfor {\n \t\tselect {\n-\t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n+\t\tcase tick := <-ticker.C:\n+\t\t\tticker.Stop()\n+\t\t\tdoRefresh(ctx, tick)",
